name: Fairchild F-27
description: The Fairchild F-27 was a popular commercial airliner from the 1950s through the 1980s during which time it became the mainstay of regional airlines across the U.S. and Europe. The F-27 could hold 48 passengers and was powered by Rolls-Royce Dart Engines. The original version of the plane was the Dutch engineered Fokker F27.
